The White House has announced that Maria Cristina "MC" González Noguera will be joining the staff as Special Assistant to the President and Communications Director to the First Lady, replacing Kristina Schake. Schake will be leaving the White House for a position in the private sector. Mrs. Obama expressed gratitude for Schake's leadership and counsel, and stated that González will bring a fresh perspective and expertise to the team. Schake praised Mrs. Obama's leadership and expressed it as an honor to have served her and the President. González Noguera is currently the Global Vice President, Corporate Communications, for the Estée Lauder Companies Inc. She has experience in strategic communications and corporate responsibility initiatives.